# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Swirl environment variables — copy to `.env` and edit.
#
# Only env vars consumed at runtime appear here. Feature configuration for
# LDAP, Keycloak/OIDC, Vault and Federation is UI-driven (Settings page) and
# persisted in the `settings` collection/bucket — it is NOT loaded from env.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------


# ==== Mode & self-identification ============================================

# MODE selects the top-level operating mode.
#   swarm      — running inside a Docker Swarm cluster, acts as federation
#                target for remote standalone portals. Default.
#   standalone — no swarm, manages remote hosts via Hosts page. Required
#                for federated portals and single-host deployments.
# Consumed by: misc/option.go (DBType/Mode bindings via config.BindEnv).
MODE=standalone

# SWIRL_CONTAINER_ID is the operator-visible override for self-deploy's
# container-identity guard. When running inside Docker, Swirl needs to
# identify its own container to refuse stack deploys that would replace
# it (except through the sidekick). Set to the container's short/full ID.
# In compose files this is typically wired to ${HOSTNAME} — Docker sets
# the hostname to the 12-char container ID by default.
# Consumed by: misc/self.go::SelfContainerID.
# Leave unset to fall back to /proc/self/cgroup parsing + os.Hostname().
# SWIRL_CONTAINER_ID=${HOSTNAME}


# ==== Storage ===============================================================

# DB_TYPE selects the DAO backend.
#   mongo — MongoDB (production, multi-replica safe).
#   bolt  — embedded BoltDB file at DB_ADDRESS (single-container only).
# Consumed by: dao/dao.go (DBType), wired via misc/option.go.
DB_TYPE=bolt

# DB_ADDRESS points at the chosen backend.
#   For mongo: `mongodb://<user:pass@><host>:<port>/<db>`
#   For bolt:  absolute path to the DB DIRECTORY (file is auto-created).
# Consumed by: dao/bolt/bolt.go::New, dao/mongo/mongo.go.
DB_ADDRESS=/data

# SWIRL_BACKUP_DIR overrides the filesystem backup destination.
# Default: /data/swirl/backups. Ignored when Settings → Backup → storage_mode
# is set to "vault" or "db".
# Consumed by: biz/backup.go::backupDir.
SWIRL_BACKUP_DIR=/data/swirl/backups


# ==== Backup encryption =====================================================

# SWIRL_BACKUP_KEY is the master passphrase for at-rest backup encryption
# (AES-256-GCM + scrypt). Must be at least 16 characters. Generate a strong
# random value, e.g. `openssl rand -base64 32 | tr -d '\n'`.
#
# If you prefer to keep secrets OUT of the environment, leave this empty
# and configure Settings → Vault → "Use Vault for backup key" so Swirl
# pulls the passphrase from a KVv2 secret at runtime.
# Consumed by: biz/backup_crypto.go::backupKeyEnv, biz/backup.go.
SWIRL_BACKUP_KEY=REQUIRED-change-me-to-a-random-32-byte-string


# ==== Swarm-only (ignored when MODE=standalone) =============================

# DOCKER_ENDPOINT is the TCP/socket URL to the Docker daemon Swirl uses
# for cluster-level operations (services, nodes, stacks). In swarm mode
# this typically points at a socat sidecar on a manager.
# Consumed by: docker/docker.go::client, wired via misc/option.go.
# DOCKER_ENDPOINT=tcp://manager_agent:2375

# DOCKER_API_VERSION pins the Docker API version. Leave unset to use the
# SDK's default with version negotiation.
# Consumed by: docker/docker.go, wired via misc/option.go.
# DOCKER_API_VERSION=1.41

# AGENTS is the comma-separated list of socat proxy services (one per node
# role). Used in swarm mode to reach per-node Docker daemons (containers,
# images, volumes are node-local).
# Consumed by: docker/docker.go::agent discovery, wired via misc/option.go.
# AGENTS=swirl_manager_agent,swirl_worker_agent


# ==== Session tokens ========================================================

# TOKEN_KEY is the HMAC secret used to sign session tokens. If unset a
# random value is generated at process start — fine for a single instance
# but breaks session validity across replicas/restarts. Set to a stable
# value in multi-replica deployments (federation targets in particular).
# Consumed by: security/*, wired via misc/option.go.
# TOKEN_KEY=change-me-to-a-random-string

# TOKEN_EXPIRY is the session lifetime (Go duration format).
# Consumed by: security/*, wired via misc/option.go. Default 30m.
# TOKEN_EXPIRY=30m


# ==== Traefik v2 ingress (optional) =========================================

# Only used by the commented-out Traefik labels in the compose templates.
# Uncomment the relevant block in compose.*.yml and set SWIRL_HOST here.
# SWIRL_HOST=swirl.example.com


# ==== Misc ==================================================================

# TZ — IANA timezone for the container (affects scheduled backup times
# and log timestamps). Default UTC.
TZ=UTC
